---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Coming Back to Yourself · Ennea Evolution"
  description="You know all your roles by heart. The person underneath them is harder to find. It's all still there, and it comes back."
>
  <div style="--accent:#EF9C20;">
    <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <p class="eyebrow">Personal Work</p>
        <h1>You know all your roles by heart. The person underneath them is harder to find.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Spouse. Parent. Employee. The responsible one. The one who handles things. You could recite the list in your sleep, because you've been living it on repeat for years.</p>
        <p>But ask what you want, what you'd do with a free Saturday and no one to answer to, and something strange happens. A pause. A flicker of an answer you talk yourself out of before it fully arrives.</p>
        <p>Not because there's nothing in you. Because what's in you got set aside so long ago you've lost easy access to it. And here's what I can tell you from doing this work: it's all still there, and it comes back. Helping someone find it again is one of my favorite things to do.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 2 · tint #FFF7E7 -->
    <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#FFF7E7;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>You might recognize this</h3>
        <ul class="marklist" style="margin-bottom:0;">
          <li>You keep saying "maybe someday" about things that matter to you.</li>
          <li>You get everything done. It just doesn't always feel like you're all the way there while you're doing it.</li>
          <li>There's a faint hollow feeling. The closest word might be homesick, except you never left.</li>
          <li>Wanting more can feel like a betrayal of a perfectly good life, so you keep it to yourself.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 3 · white -->
    <section class="panel">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>What happened</h3>
        <p>Nothing dramatic. Life happened around you, and you did what each season asked. Kids needed raising. Careers needed building. Bills needed paying. Every time a want of yours collided with a duty, the duty won, and at the time it often had to.</p>
        <p>Postponing yourself doesn't feel painful at first. It feels practical. But the dial isn't selective. Turn down what you want for long enough, and the joy and the color turn down with it.</p>
        <blockquote class="pullquote">The part of you that feels most like you isn't gone. It's just been waiting for a season that never got scheduled.</blockquote>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What the work is</h3>
        <p>We schedule the season.</p>
        <p>It starts with listening, not overhauling. The wanting got quiet slowly, and it comes back the same way. What sounds good. What feels true. What you want, without immediately explaining why it won't work.</p>
        <p>None of this means tearing down the life you built. You keep every role you have. You just stop being only them.</p>
        <div class="photo" style="margin-top:2.25rem;">
          <img src="/img/into-the-light.jpg" alt="A person stepping out into bright morning light" width="960" height="640" loading="lazy" />
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top:2.5rem;">What changes</h3>
        <p>You start showing up in your own life again. Your name appears on your calendar for reasons that have nothing to do with anyone else's needs. You notice what you like. You hear what you want. You stop needing permission to care about it.</p>
        <p>And the question underneath everything, not "What's expected of me?" but "What do I want?", finally gets answers. That's the strangest, best part. You always had them.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PANEL 4 · white · close -->
    <section class="panel center" style="padding-top:0;">
      <div class="container narrow">
        <h3>Start here</h3>
        <p>You don't have to arrive with answers. Just bring the part of you that wonders if there might be more.</p>
        <a href="/get-started" class="btn" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">Get Started</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
